      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPIRIT OF LUNA (11) stepped up to 1500m last time out and was very good on the Scarpside at Pinjarra, beaten 1.5L when sitting just off the speed. This looks to shape similarly and she'll carry no weight after the claim of Murray. Can sit handy from the draw and go a couple better this time around. WHERE'S MY LUNCH (4) led and folded last time out at Albany in a disappointing performance. The inside draw should see him close to the speed again and if he can return to his best form, he can feature in the finish. BENTLEY BEAU (6) was 2.9L off the winner last time out at Geraldton when second-up and out to this track and trip. Likely to get back from the wide draw again today, but he'll be better again third-up and some gear changes can see him turn in an improved effort. CANTILEVER (3) is on the quick turnaround and he can bounce back to his best coming back to the mile. ALTERNO (7) won't be far away if he can run up to his recent efforts.",
